    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, melt a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 3-4 min or until a smooth, very thick sauce remains, then set aside – this is your <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
