    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chips are ready, transfer the baking tray with the chips to the bottom shelf of the oven</p><p>Preheat the grill to high</p><p>Transfer the <strong>crispy chicken </strong>to a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray and top with the <strong>béchamel sauce</strong>,<strong> </strong>then the<strong> grated cheese </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 3-5 min or until the cheese is melted and golden – this is your <strong>Teesside parmo</strong></p>",
